An injured person is assisted after an incident on Westminster Bridge in London, Britain March 22, 2017. Image: REUTERS REUTERS/Toby Melville Shots have been fired outside the UK Parliament in an incident UK police are treating as &#8220;terrorist&#8221; related. According to the AFP newswire British police said the incident outside Parliament on Wednesday which saw a police officer stabbed and his assailant shot was being treated as terrorism. &#8220;We are treating this as a terrorist incident until we know otherwise &#8221; police said in a statement. Earlier the BBC tweeted that the Palace of Westminster was reportedly in lockdown. Live images on television showed a huge police presence outside the Parliament building. News RT &#8220;A car on Westminster Bridge has just mowed down at least 5 people.&#8221; &#8220;My prayers are with the victims.&#8221; Mr. R. Sikorski #London pic.twitter.com/lPYqenXhw9 Thumbelina Valkyrie (@ThumbelinaIQ) March 22, 2017 This is a developing story. Related Share on Facebook Share Share on Twitter Tweet Share on Google Plus Share